# How to use this guide in your Open Group

This document is designed for the **{{ open_groups_name }}** of **{{ church_name }}** — the groups that meet at home during the week to study, pray and share life.

## Before the meeting (leader)

1. Read the **Executive summary** and the **Key points** ahead of time.
2. Check the **Scripture references** — keep a Bible handy or open [YouVersion](https://www.bible.com/).
3. Pick the **main question** you want to explore (there are 3 on the cards — don't feel you must do them all).
4. Prepare a short **ice-breaker** (5 min) linked to the theme.

## During the meeting (suggested flow)

| Moment | What happens |
|--------|--------------|
| **Welcome** | Greet everyone, quick check-in. |
| **Ice-break** | A light question or game to warm the room. |
| **One song (worship)** | A single song together — sets the heart posture. |
| **Theme sharing** | The leader walks through the key points of the message. |
| **Discussion** | Choose from the 3 cards at the end of the guide — go deep, take your time. |
| **Closing prayer** | Pray for one another; release the week. |
| **Coffee (if any)** | Stay for coffee/dessert if the host offers. |

## After

- Write the week's commitment on the question card.
- Next time, start with: **"How did the challenge go?"**

---

_May your meetings be times of **open heavens** over your homes._
